@startuml Restart Strategies - ONE_FOR_ONE vs ONE_FOR_ALL vs REST_FOR_ONE

title Restart Strategies: Comparing Supervisor Recovery Modes

== ONE_FOR_ONE: Isolated Restart ==

participant "Supervisor" as sup1
participant "Child A" as childA
participant "Child B" as childB
participant "Child C" as childC

sup1 -> childA: spawn
sup1 -> childB: spawn
sup1 -> childC: spawn

childB -> childB: CRASH!
sup1 -> childB: restart childB only
note right of sup1
  A: still running ✓
  B: restarted (new process)
  C: still running ✓
end note

== ONE_FOR_ALL: Restart All ==

participant "Supervisor" as sup2
participant "Worker A" as workerA
participant "Worker B" as workerB
participant "Worker C" as workerC

sup2 -> workerA: spawn
sup2 -> workerB: spawn
sup2 -> workerC: spawn

workerB -> workerB: CRASH!
sup2 -> workerA: stop
sup2 -> workerB: stop
sup2 -> workerC: stop
note right of sup2
  All children stopped
  (shutdown signal)
end note

sup2 -> workerA: spawn (new)
sup2 -> workerB: spawn (new)
sup2 -> workerC: spawn (new)
note right of sup2
  A: restarted (fresh state)
  B: restarted (fresh state)
  C: restarted (fresh state)
  Use case: shared resource pool
end note

== REST_FOR_ONE: Cascade Restart ==

participant "Supervisor" as sup3
participant "Parent" as parent
participant "Child 1" as child1
participant "Child 2" as child2
participant "Child 3" as child3

sup3 -> parent: spawn
sup3 -> child1: spawn(depends on parent)
sup3 -> child2: spawn(depends on child1)
sup3 -> child3: spawn(depends on child2)

child1 -> child1: CRASH!
sup3 -> child1: stop
sup3 -> child2: stop (depends on child1)
sup3 -> child3: stop (depends on child2)
note right of sup3
  Parent: still running ✓
  Child 1: restarted
  Child 2: restarted
  Child 3: restarted
  Use case: dependency chain
end note
